      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:2:13:6",
      "text": [
        " تَقْعُدُ النُّفَسَاءُ أَيَّامَهَا الَّتِي كَانَتْ تَقْعُدُ فِي الْحَيْضِ وَ تَسْتَظْهِرُ بِيَوْمَيْنِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Fazzal, from Ibn Bukeyr, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The woman with post-childbirth bleeding (<span class=\"iTxt\">Nafsa’a</span>) would sit (abstaining) for her days which she used to sit (abstaining) during the menstruation (<span class=\"iTxt\">Haydh</span>), and she would examine in two days’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from ibn Faddal from ibn Bukayr from Zurarah who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘A woman for giving birth waits for the number of days of her Hayd (menses); then she must examine in two days.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
